1
00:01:40,849 --> 00:01:45,013
We're very proud of Judah Rosenthal's
philanthropic efforts...

2
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:49,384
...his endless hours of fundraising
for the hospital...

3
00:01:49,591 --> 00:01:51,559
...the new medical center...

4
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:53,591
...and the ophthalmology wing...

5
00:01:53,795 --> 00:01:56,992
...which, until this year,
had just been a dream.

6
00:01:57,432 --> 00:02:01,732
But it's Judah Rosenthal, our friend,
that we most appreciate.

7
00:02:01,936 --> 00:02:05,667
The husband, the father,
the golf companion.

8
00:02:05,874 --> 00:02:08,502
-For medical problems...
-You're blushing.

9
00:02:08,710 --> 00:02:13,704
...call him day or night, weekends,
or holidays. But you can also call...

10
00:02:13,915 --> 00:02:18,318
...to ask about the best restaurant
in Paris. Or Athens.

11
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:21,182
Or which hotel to stay at in Moscow.

12
00:02:21,389 --> 00:02:25,485
Or the best recording
of a particular Mozart symphony.

13
00:02:25,693 --> 00:02:28,821
My father is so nervous
about having to speak.

14
00:02:29,030 --> 00:02:33,262
l knew he was nervous when you didn't
eat any cocktail weenies.

15
00:02:33,468 --> 00:02:37,404
He was so courageous all week.
Then suddenly tonight, stage fright.

16
00:02:37,605 --> 00:02:41,507
Judah, you were fine till you
got home from work today.

17
00:02:41,943 --> 00:02:42,932
Any mail?

18
00:02:43,144 --> 00:02:45,874
The mail's where
l left it this morning.

19
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:48,275
l haven't had a second all day.

20
00:02:48,483 --> 00:02:52,078
lf you're gonna shower, do it.
l have to use it too.

21
00:02:53,154 --> 00:02:55,622
l dread making that speech tonight.

22
00:03:18,413 --> 00:03:21,382
Dear Miriam Rosenthal,'

23
00:03:21,583 --> 00:03:25,815
I'm at the lowest point of my life
as I write you this letter,

24
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:30,548
I wish to cause no suffering,
but because I'm going through hell,,,

25
00:03:30,758 --> 00:03:33,420
,,,I ask if you can meet me one time,

26
00:03:34,128 --> 00:03:37,393
Your husband and I
are more than friends,,,

27
00:03:37,599 --> 00:03:42,036
,,,and have been deeply in love
for over two years now,

28
00:03:42,237 --> 00:03:43,534
This must be faced,,,

29
00:03:43,738 --> 00:03:47,196
,,,as there are many
ramifications and complications,

30
00:03:47,408 --> 00:03:50,400
Many promises were made, et cetera,

31
00:03:50,845 --> 00:03:54,337
I need an open exchange
with you to clear things,

32
00:03:54,549 --> 00:03:56,414
For all of us to go on,,,

33
00:03:56,618 --> 00:04:00,918
,,, the situation has got to be
confronted in some fashion,

34
00:04:01,122 --> 00:04:04,023
Please contact me at this number,

35
00:04:04,225 --> 00:04:06,785
I want what's best for everyone,

36
00:04:06,995 --> 00:04:08,690
Dolores Paley,

37
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:36,787
That the new ophthalmology wing
has become a reality...

38
00:04:36,991 --> 00:04:40,859
...is not just a tribute to me
but to a spirit of community...

39
00:04:41,062 --> 00:04:44,998
...generosity, of mutual caring
and answered prayers.

40
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:49,032
lt's funny l use the term
''answered prayers.''

41
00:04:49,237 --> 00:04:50,795
l'm a man of science.

42
00:04:51,005 --> 00:04:54,964
l've always been a skeptic,
but l was raised religiously.

43
00:04:55,176 --> 00:04:57,474
l challenged it, even as a child...

44
00:04:58,179 --> 00:05:01,205
,,,but some of that feeling
stuck with me,

45
00:05:01,849 --> 00:05:04,215
I remember my father telling me,'

46
00:05:04,419 --> 00:05:07,286
''The eyes of God are on us always, ''

47
00:05:07,789 --> 00:05:09,484
''The eyes of God.''

48
00:05:10,391 --> 00:05:13,121
What a phrase to a young boy.

49
00:05:13,328 --> 00:05:15,956
l mean, what were God's eyes like?

50
00:05:16,297 --> 00:05:20,734
Unimaginably penetrating,
intense eyes, l assumed.

51
00:05:21,603 --> 00:05:26,939
l wonder if it was just a coincidence
that l specialized in ophthalmology.

52
00:05:29,544 --> 00:05:33,810
l'm so proud of you, Judah.
Sharon is, we all are.

53
00:05:34,582 --> 00:05:36,174
All together.

54
00:06:00,608 --> 00:06:04,203
-Why did you write the letter?
-We've been through it.

55
00:06:04,412 --> 00:06:06,539
You wanna destroy my family?

56
00:06:06,748 --> 00:06:09,114
l want her to know her husband.

57
00:06:09,317 --> 00:06:13,913
lt was lying there all day.
By sheer chance, she didn't open it.

58
00:06:14,122 --> 00:06:17,148
You said you'd leave Miriam!
We made plans!

59
00:06:17,358 --> 00:06:18,484
-l didn't.
-You did!

60
00:06:18,693 --> 00:06:20,422
l gave up opportunities!

61
00:06:20,628 --> 00:06:22,926
-Pipe dreams.
-Other men wanted me.

62
00:06:23,131 --> 00:06:25,964
What do you want?
You think this is easy?

63
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:29,659
l want what you told me
you wanted, to be together.

64
00:06:29,871 --> 00:06:33,671
Otherwise, l don't know what!
l'll jump out the window!

65
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:38,005
You've been my whole life
for two years. l can't go back.

66
00:06:38,212 --> 00:06:40,305
You turned my life around!

67
00:06:40,515 --> 00:06:43,279
l never said l'd leave Miriam.

68
00:06:43,484 --> 00:06:46,920
''There's no passion left.''
Those are your words...

69
00:06:47,121 --> 00:06:50,955
...unless you lied.
Or there's something l don't know.

70
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:55,459
-Have you met someone else?
-What? For God's sake, Dolores.

71
00:06:55,697 --> 00:06:57,392
-Dolores--
-What?

72
00:06:57,632 --> 00:06:58,929
Now, look.

73
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:03,229
l've lived with her 25 years.
The roots are very deep.

74
00:07:03,438 --> 00:07:05,497
l can't go on leading two lives.

75
00:07:05,707 --> 00:07:10,303
You're not doing her a favor by
pretending. l won't be without you.

76
00:07:10,511 --> 00:07:14,607
This won't happen without a fight!
l wanna speak to Miriam!

77
00:07:14,816 --> 00:07:16,807
-Nothing's happening, okay?
-No!

78
00:07:17,018 --> 00:07:19,384
Yes! Listen to me, please.

79
00:07:19,587 --> 00:07:23,648
We'll work something out.
Let me get my thoughts together.

80
00:07:23,858 --> 00:07:26,019
Just don't do anything rash.

81
00:07:26,227 --> 00:07:27,592
Dolores.

82
00:07:29,464 --> 00:07:30,488
What?

83
00:07:34,001 --> 00:07:35,593
lt's gonna be okay.

84
00:07:38,372 --> 00:07:39,999
Oh, God.

85
00:07:41,175 --> 00:07:42,767
-You were gonna wait--
-Annie--

86
00:07:42,977 --> 00:07:45,844
-Then throw me aside!
-Don't dramatize,

87
00:07:46,047 --> 00:07:50,108
I've given you the best years
of my life!

88
00:07:50,318 --> 00:07:51,376
Get out of here!

89
00:07:51,586 --> 00:07:54,282
I know what you are,
Lucky I found out!

90
00:07:54,489 --> 00:07:56,514
Those are my clothes!

91
00:08:00,128 --> 00:08:01,425
That was great.

92
00:08:01,629 --> 00:08:04,462
-The tuxedos, the evening gowns.
-Great.

93
00:08:04,665 --> 00:08:08,101
lt was wonderful to live like that.
This is awful.

94
00:08:08,302 --> 00:08:11,396
Let me get a cab. You stay here.

95
00:08:11,606 --> 00:08:15,508
-You wanna see a movie again tomorrow?
-Sure, Uncle Cliff.

96
00:08:15,710 --> 00:08:16,699
Jesus.

97
00:08:16,911 --> 00:08:20,005
Unless maybe we should
make it a museum day.

98
00:08:20,214 --> 00:08:25,117
l promised your dad on his deathbed
you'd get a well-rounded education.

99
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:29,050
We probably shouldn't
go to the movies every day...

100
00:08:29,257 --> 00:08:30,884
...even though l'd love to.

101
00:08:31,092 --> 00:08:33,060
While we wait for a cab...

102
00:08:33,261 --> 00:08:35,821
...l'll give you
your lesson for today.

103
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:37,554
Your lesson is this:

104
00:08:37,765 --> 00:08:40,495
Don't listen to what
your teachers say.

105
00:08:40,701 --> 00:08:42,794
Just see what they look like.

106
00:08:43,004 --> 00:08:46,235
Then you'll know what life
will really be like.

107
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:49,637
You heard it here first.
l see a cab. lf we run...

108
00:08:49,844 --> 00:08:53,569
...we can kick the crutch
from that old lady and get it.

109
00:08:55,604 --> 00:08:58,300
-l'm back!
-Where were you?

110
00:08:58,507 --> 00:09:02,603
-Just out and around.
-Took your niece to a movie again.

111
00:09:02,811 --> 00:09:05,974
l'm crazy about that kid.
She's just great.

112
00:09:06,181 --> 00:09:09,878
My brother's in town.
He asked us to a dinner party.

113
00:09:10,085 --> 00:09:13,452
-Jesus.
-Please. You gonna make another scene?

114
00:09:13,655 --> 00:09:17,853
-l didn't do that last time.
-You did. Your resentment showed.

115
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:23,327
l don't resent him. He's a pompous ass.
You don't see it since you love him.

116
00:09:23,532 --> 00:09:25,193
-What did you say?
-Nothing.

117
00:09:25,401 --> 00:09:27,892
You did. You're running down Lester.

118
00:09:28,103 --> 00:09:31,561
-l like your brother Ben.
-You're not jealous of him.

119
00:09:31,774 --> 00:09:34,607
l'm jealous because
he's a TV producer?

120
00:09:34,810 --> 00:09:38,610
No. Because he's highly respected
and he's a millionaire...

121
00:09:38,814 --> 00:09:41,180
...and doing what you'd like to do.

122
00:09:41,383 --> 00:09:44,841
Listen, l can't watch his stuff.
lt's submental.

123
00:09:45,054 --> 00:09:48,785
-He wants to talk to you about a job.
-l don't need one.

124
00:09:48,991 --> 00:09:51,459
Didn't l get honorable mention at--?

125
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:54,561
The Cincinnati Documentary
Film Festival?

126
00:09:54,763 --> 00:09:58,426
Everybody got honorable mention
who showed up.

127
00:09:58,634 --> 00:10:01,660
Boy, things have really
changed around here.

128
00:10:10,179 --> 00:10:12,409
Wendy, Cliff, meet Lisa.

129
00:10:12,614 --> 00:10:15,777
My sister, Wendy.
My brother-in-law, Clifford.

130
00:10:15,984 --> 00:10:19,784
-Lisa's starring in my new series.
-Not really starring.

131
00:10:19,988 --> 00:10:23,651
You're one of the stars.
lt's an ensemble piece.

132
00:10:23,859 --> 00:10:26,225
-Hello, Lester.
-Hello, darling.

133
00:10:26,428 --> 00:10:29,591
-So glad you came.
-Thank you for inviting me.

134
00:10:29,798 --> 00:10:33,029
Have a drink. l'll be right there.

135
00:10:33,235 --> 00:10:36,898
She gave a bundle to
The Museum of Broadcasting.

136
00:10:37,739 --> 00:10:41,140
-She plays a--
-A lawyer for the ACLU.

137
00:10:41,343 --> 00:10:43,868
Married to a conservative writer.

138
00:10:44,079 --> 00:10:47,412
-So we can get into issues.
-We'll try to be fair.

139
00:10:47,616 --> 00:10:50,949
But knowing Lester,
he'll slant it to the left.

140
00:10:51,153 --> 00:10:52,177
Let's hope so.

141
00:10:52,387 --> 00:10:54,855
-We're shooting here.
-You'll be here?

142
00:10:55,057 --> 00:10:57,321
l wanna shoot more in New York.

143
00:10:57,526 --> 00:10:59,460
-Oh, great.
-l love this town.

144
00:10:59,661 --> 00:11:02,789
Out there is such
a Mickey Mouse environment.

145
00:11:02,998 --> 00:11:04,397
The reason l'm here--

146
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:08,263
-Hello, Lester.
-l wanna talk to you. Don't go away.

147
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:11,598
A bunch of us are getting together...

148
00:11:11,807 --> 00:11:14,537
...to build a studio here in the city.

149
00:11:14,743 --> 00:11:18,042
ln fact-- l'm sorry,
just give me one second.

150
00:11:18,247 --> 00:11:19,680
ldea for series:

151
00:11:19,882 --> 00:11:23,215
A high-profile builder,
with grandiose dreams...

152
00:11:23,418 --> 00:11:26,387
...a lá Donald Trump.
Shot in New York.

153
00:11:26,588 --> 00:11:29,386
-Look who's here.
-That's my brother Ben.

154
00:11:29,591 --> 00:11:33,118
Ben, Carol, come here.
Hi, kid. Nice to see you.

155
00:11:34,029 --> 00:11:35,690
-Hi, honey.
-Hi, sweetheart.

156
00:11:35,898 --> 00:11:38,992
-Hi, Cliff.
-How you doing? How are your eyes?

157
00:11:39,201 --> 00:11:41,999
Not so good. lt's not so optimistic.

158
00:11:42,204 --> 00:11:44,468
l've been seeing Dr. Rosenthal.

159
00:11:44,673 --> 00:11:47,642
Lester, don't you want
to talk to Clifford?

160
00:11:47,843 --> 00:11:50,437
Oh, yeah. Step into my office.

161
00:11:51,847 --> 00:11:55,078
-Hi, l'm Lisa.
-Hi. We didn't meet. l'm sorry.

162
00:11:55,284 --> 00:11:58,720
-So are you in TV too?
-No.

163
00:11:58,921 --> 00:12:00,752
No. l'm a rabbi.

164
00:12:01,557 --> 00:12:04,424
You don't wear an outfit or anything?

165
00:12:04,993 --> 00:12:07,985
Public television wants to do
a documentary...

166
00:12:08,197 --> 00:12:10,495
...on the way l talk and think--

167
00:12:10,699 --> 00:12:13,896
lt's part of their
Creative Mind series.

168
00:12:14,102 --> 00:12:16,400
So l told them about you.

169
00:12:16,605 --> 00:12:19,267
Thanks. l'm working on my own thing.

170
00:12:19,474 --> 00:12:21,499
-A little film.
-Wendy told me.

171
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:26,238
A film about some philosophy
professor, which is admirable.

172
00:12:26,448 --> 00:12:31,078
But this is a chance to earn
decent money, reach a big audience.

173
00:12:31,286 --> 00:12:34,380
Last thing you need
is me as your biographer.

174
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:38,959
l make these little films on
toxic waste and starving children.

175
00:12:39,161 --> 00:12:43,757
l'll be frank. You're not my
first choice. lt's a favor to Wendy.

176
00:12:43,966 --> 00:12:48,733
-You never work. She's embarrassed.
-l've worked, but nobody pays me.

177
00:12:48,937 --> 00:12:51,462
l know you don't respect what l do.

178
00:12:51,673 --> 00:12:54,107
But l got a closet full of Emmys.

179
00:12:54,309 --> 00:12:57,506
You think that's bullshit.
Fine. l understand.

180
00:12:57,713 --> 00:13:01,205
Maybe l could use the money
to finish my movie.

181
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:03,111
l do have some debts.

182
00:13:03,318 --> 00:13:04,683
ldea for farce:

183
00:13:04,886 --> 00:13:09,220
A poor loser agrees to do
the story of a great man's life.

184
00:13:09,424 --> 00:13:12,359
And in the process,
he learns deep values.

185
00:13:15,597 --> 00:13:19,533
-What takes you to Boston?
-I'm lecturing at a symposium,

186
00:13:19,735 --> 00:13:22,135
lncidentally, my name's Dolores.

187
00:13:22,337 --> 00:13:24,032
-Hello, Dolores.
-Hello.

188
00:13:24,239 --> 00:13:26,332
-Pretty name.
-Thank you.

189
00:13:26,975 --> 00:13:30,342
-Do you go to Boston often?
-Not very often,

190
00:13:30,545 --> 00:13:33,343
I don't know anyone
in Boston, actually,

191
00:13:33,548 --> 00:13:34,981
-Really?
-Yeah,

192
00:13:43,358 --> 00:13:44,347
-Morning.
-Hi.

193
00:13:44,559 --> 00:13:47,528
A Miss Paley called,
said it was urgent.

194
00:13:53,669 --> 00:13:57,537
Why did you phone me?
l told you l'd call you.

195
00:13:57,739 --> 00:14:01,766
l couldn't help it.
l was going out of my skin.

196
00:14:03,712 --> 00:14:05,680
l have to see you later.

197
00:14:06,081 --> 00:14:07,605
l have to!

198
00:14:09,051 --> 00:14:10,177
Okay.

199
00:14:11,186 --> 00:14:13,086
After work is okay.

200
00:14:16,358 --> 00:14:17,552
l see it.

201
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:19,749
Yeah.

202
00:14:20,762 --> 00:14:22,024
l see it.

203
00:14:23,465 --> 00:14:25,399
Oh, God.

204
00:14:26,168 --> 00:14:27,328
What?

205
00:14:28,804 --> 00:14:30,704
l need to take a minute.

206
00:14:33,108 --> 00:14:34,575
What's wrong, Judah?

207
00:14:36,111 --> 00:14:38,204
l'm in such trouble, Ben.

208
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,811
What is it?

209
00:14:40,882 --> 00:14:43,009
l need to talk to someone.

210
00:14:43,552 --> 00:14:44,678
Sure.

211
00:14:46,054 --> 00:14:49,956
l've known you for years.
You're religious. l'm not.

212
00:14:50,158 --> 00:14:53,958
We've differed on many points,
but l do respect you.

213
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:57,665
-May l confide in you?
-Of course.

214
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:01,094
Go ahead. Everything's confidential.

215
00:15:05,407 --> 00:15:07,637
l've done a foolish thing.

216
00:15:07,843 --> 00:15:09,640
Senseless. Vain.

217
00:15:09,845 --> 00:15:11,039
Dumb.

218
00:15:14,549 --> 00:15:16,107
Another woman.

219
00:15:20,522 --> 00:15:24,925
Maybe l was flattered, vulnerable.

220
00:15:25,127 --> 00:15:27,857
Maybe because she was
helpless and alone.

221
00:15:28,063 --> 00:15:30,964
But now my life's
about to go up in smoke.

222
00:15:31,466 --> 00:15:35,027
-Can't you break it off?
-The woman won't allow it.

223
00:15:35,537 --> 00:15:38,370
She's young. She's very unstable.

224
00:15:38,573 --> 00:15:40,097
She's an hysteric.

225
00:15:40,475 --> 00:15:42,033
And vindictive.

226
00:15:42,277 --> 00:15:43,835
And it's my fault.

227
00:15:44,045 --> 00:15:47,105
l instigated it. l prolonged it.

228
00:15:47,315 --> 00:15:50,409
l tried to back off,
but l was too weak.

229
00:15:50,619 --> 00:15:53,213
But l promised her nothing.

230
00:15:53,422 --> 00:15:56,220
But did l? l don't even know anymore.

231
00:15:56,425 --> 00:15:59,417
ln the heat of passion,
you say things.

232
00:15:59,628 --> 00:16:02,825
After two years of living
this double life...

233
00:16:03,031 --> 00:16:05,295
...l awakened as if from a dream...

234
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:09,300
-...and realized what l'd be losing.
-lt's called wisdom.

235
00:16:09,504 --> 00:16:11,631
lt comes to some suddenly.

236
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:15,833
We realize the difference between
what's deep and lasting...

237
00:16:16,044 --> 00:16:19,377
...versus the superficial
payoff of the moment.

238
00:16:19,581 --> 00:16:23,881
l kidded myself about loving her,
but deep down l knew.

239
00:16:24,085 --> 00:16:26,212
Knowing l behaved selfishly...

240
00:16:26,421 --> 00:16:28,981
...for pleasure,
for adventure, for lust.

241
00:16:29,191 --> 00:16:31,853
Sometimes, when there's real love...

242
00:16:32,060 --> 00:16:35,154
...and true acknowledgment
of a mistake...

243
00:16:35,363 --> 00:16:37,729
