-Like Hitler?

955
01:10:54,012 --> 01:10:55,479
We're having a Seder!

956
01:10:55,680 --> 01:10:58,808
Six million Jews killed,
they got away with it.

957
01:10:59,017 --> 01:11:02,077
-How'd they get away with it?
-Open your eyes!

958
01:11:02,287 --> 01:11:05,313
Six million Jews.
They got off with nothing.

959
01:11:05,524 --> 01:11:08,891
-How could men do such a thing?
-Might makes right.

960
01:11:09,094 --> 01:11:13,360
-Until the Americans--
-l don't like this talk at Seder.

961
01:11:13,565 --> 01:11:14,827
Okay! All right!

962
01:11:15,033 --> 01:11:18,594
-I think this is interesting,
-Yeah, you do,

963
01:11:18,804 --> 01:11:20,601
There's this joke,

964
01:11:20,806 --> 01:11:22,967
A prizefighter enters the ring.

965
01:11:23,175 --> 01:11:26,633
His brother asks the family priest
to pray for him.

966
01:11:26,845 --> 01:11:30,281
He said, ''Okay.
But if he can punch, it'll help.''

967
01:11:30,482 --> 01:11:34,885
So you're saying you challenge
the moral structure of everything?

968
01:11:35,087 --> 01:11:39,148
Moral structure? You use
that nonsense on your pupils?

969
01:11:39,357 --> 01:11:42,588
You don't find human impulses
basically decent?

970
01:11:42,794 --> 01:11:47,356
-There's basically nothing.
-A cynic, a nihilist. Back to Russia.

971
01:11:47,566 --> 01:11:50,933
Well, listen. l happen
to agree with May...

972
01:11:51,136 --> 01:11:53,195
...when it comes to mumbo jumbo.

973
01:11:53,405 --> 01:11:57,136
But you come to every Seder.
You pray in Hebrew.

974
01:11:57,342 --> 01:12:01,278
l go through the motions.
Like any ritual, it's a habit.

975
01:12:01,480 --> 01:12:05,541
So you say there's no morality
anywhere in the whole world?

976
01:12:05,750 --> 01:12:10,210
For those who want it, it's there.
Nothing's handed down in stone.

977
01:12:10,422 --> 01:12:12,515
Sol's kind of faith is a gift.

978
01:12:12,724 --> 01:12:15,852
lt's like an ear for music
or talent to draw.

979
01:12:16,061 --> 01:12:19,724
You use logic on him all day
and he still believes.

980
01:12:19,931 --> 01:12:23,924
-Must everything be logical?
-And if a man commits a crime?

981
01:12:24,136 --> 01:12:25,694
lf he--

982
01:12:25,904 --> 01:12:27,337
lf he kills?

983
01:12:28,473 --> 01:12:32,136
-ln some way, he'll be punished.
-lf he's caught, Sol.

984
01:12:32,344 --> 01:12:36,940
''What originates from a black deed
will blossom in a foul manner.''

985
01:12:37,149 --> 01:12:40,277
You're relying too heavily
on the Bible.

986
01:12:40,485 --> 01:12:44,922
Whether it's the Old Testament
or Shakespeare, murder will out.

987
01:12:45,123 --> 01:12:48,650
-Who said anything about murder?
-You did.

988
01:12:51,096 --> 01:12:52,427
Did l?

989
01:12:54,666 --> 01:12:57,601
l say, if he can do it
and get away with it...

990
01:12:57,802 --> 01:13:01,704
...and chooses not to be bothered
by ethics, he's home free.

991
01:13:01,907 --> 01:13:04,637
History is written by the winners.

992
01:13:04,843 --> 01:13:08,574
Had the Nazis won,
future generations would understand...

993
01:13:08,780 --> 01:13:10,941
...World War ll quite differently.

994
01:13:11,149 --> 01:13:15,017
Your aunt is brilliant,
but she's had an unhappy life.

995
01:13:15,220 --> 01:13:20,419
And if all your faith is wrong--
l mean, just what if? lf?

996
01:13:20,625 --> 01:13:23,753
l'll still have a better life
than doubters.

997
01:13:23,962 --> 01:13:27,955
Wait a minute. Are you saying
you prefer God to the truth?

998
01:13:28,166 --> 01:13:33,001
-l'll always choose God over truth.
-l agree with him.

999
01:13:33,638 --> 01:13:36,505
l say, what goes around comes around.

1000
01:13:41,613 --> 01:13:46,016
-You okay? l was worried. lt's late.
-l had some business.

1001
01:13:46,218 --> 01:13:47,708
Mrs. Ames is waiting.

1002
01:13:47,919 --> 01:13:50,251
-Any messages?
-You got an odd one.

1003
01:13:50,455 --> 01:13:53,720
A Detective O'Donnell
wanted to talk to you.

1004
01:13:53,925 --> 01:13:58,487
l tried to ask him what about,
but he only wants to talk with you.

1005
01:14:18,316 --> 01:14:21,945
-lt's not a great movie, but it's fun.
-l liked it.

1006
01:14:22,153 --> 01:14:24,485
Maybe l want to be an actress.

1007
01:14:24,689 --> 01:14:29,592
l don't want you to be an actress.
Be on the Supreme Court or a doctor.

1008
01:14:29,794 --> 01:14:31,921
Show business is dog-eat-dog.

1009
01:14:32,130 --> 01:14:37,067
lt's worse than dog-eat-dog. lt's
dog-doesn't-return-other-dog's-calls.

1010
01:14:37,269 --> 01:14:39,294
l should check my service.

1011
01:14:39,504 --> 01:14:42,302
l don't know why.
l never have messages.

1012
01:14:42,507 --> 01:14:46,034
-l call, l hear the girls giggling.
-How's Halley?

1013
01:14:46,244 --> 01:14:49,042
She's great. l'm gonna make my move.

1014
01:14:49,247 --> 01:14:53,343
But l have this ethical dilemma
because l'm married.

1015
01:14:53,551 --> 01:14:56,520
Clifford Stern. Any messages?
Can you check?

1016
01:14:56,721 --> 01:14:59,656
My heart says one thing.
My head, another.

1017
01:14:59,858 --> 01:15:03,589
lt's hard to get your heart
and head together in life.

1018
01:15:03,795 --> 01:15:06,764
ln my case, they're not
even friendly. Yes?

1019
01:15:10,635 --> 01:15:12,068
Really?

1020
01:15:17,709 --> 01:15:19,142
No.

1021
01:15:21,680 --> 01:15:23,204
Okay. Thank you.

1022
01:15:26,751 --> 01:15:28,082
What's wrong?

1023
01:15:31,389 --> 01:15:33,323
Professor Levy...

1024
01:15:33,658 --> 01:15:35,785
...committed suicide.

1025
01:15:37,028 --> 01:15:39,326
But we must always remember,,,

1026
01:15:39,531 --> 01:15:43,126
,,, that we--
When we are born,,,

1027
01:15:43,335 --> 01:15:45,963
,,,we need a great deal of love,,,

1028
01:15:46,171 --> 01:15:49,766
,,,in order to persuade us
to stay in life,

1029
01:15:49,974 --> 01:15:53,774
Once we get that love,
it usually lasts us,

1030
01:15:53,978 --> 01:15:56,606
But the universe is a cold place,

1031
01:15:56,815 --> 01:16:00,273
It's we who invest it
with our feelings,

1032
01:16:00,485 --> 01:16:03,147
And under certain conditions,,,

1033
01:16:03,355 --> 01:16:06,950
,,,we feel that the thing
isn't worth it anymore,

1034
01:16:07,158 --> 01:16:11,720
l came as soon as l heard. l thought
you wouldn't want to be alone.

1035
01:16:11,930 --> 01:16:16,390
God, it's been terrible. l called--
The guy was not sick at all.

1036
01:16:16,601 --> 01:16:20,264
He left a note that said,
''l've gone out the window.''

1037
01:16:20,472 --> 01:16:24,738
A major intellectual, and this
is his note. What does it mean?

1038
01:16:24,943 --> 01:16:26,410
He was a role model.

1039
01:16:26,611 --> 01:16:31,571
-You'd think he'd leave a decent note.
-Did he have family or anything?

1040
01:16:31,783 --> 01:16:36,652
They were killed in the war. lt's
strange. He's seen the worst in life.

1041
01:16:36,855 --> 01:16:41,019
He always said yes to life.
Now today he said no.

1042
01:16:41,226 --> 01:16:44,855
lmagine his students,
how shattered they will be.

1043
01:16:45,063 --> 01:16:49,022
Where l grew up, in Brooklyn,
nobody committed suicide.

1044
01:16:49,234 --> 01:16:53,534
-Everyone was too unhappy.
-This will put a damper on the show.

1045
01:16:53,738 --> 01:16:56,730
l got 600,000 feet of film
on this guy...

1046
01:16:56,941 --> 01:16:59,535
...and he's telling how great life is.

1047
01:16:59,744 --> 01:17:02,474
l'll cut it up,
use it for guitar picks.

1048
01:17:02,680 --> 01:17:05,615
l was thinking,
no matter how elaborate...

1049
01:17:05,817 --> 01:17:08,581
...a philosophical system
you work out...

1050
01:17:08,787 --> 01:17:12,188
...in the end,
it's gotta be incomplete.

1051
01:17:12,390 --> 01:17:16,486
l've been so annoyed all day.
l'm sorry for seeming cranky.

1052
01:17:16,694 --> 01:17:21,188
No, l understand. l just thought
you might want some company.

1053
01:17:24,235 --> 01:17:26,135
No. Don't do that.

1054
01:17:26,704 --> 01:17:29,639
lt's something l've wanted
to do for weeks.

1055
01:17:29,841 --> 01:17:31,900
-You must know.
-You're married.

1056
01:17:32,110 --> 01:17:33,407
Yes, l'm married.

1057
01:17:33,611 --> 01:17:36,944
But, you know, that's
not gonna last. l mean....

1058
01:17:37,148 --> 01:17:38,513
Well, you know...

1059
01:17:38,716 --> 01:17:40,911
...l'm not ready.

1060
01:17:42,654 --> 01:17:45,487
ls there something you're
not telling me?

1061
01:17:45,690 --> 01:17:46,679
No.

1062
01:17:46,891 --> 01:17:49,951
ls there someone else?
Don't say it's Lester.

1063
01:17:50,161 --> 01:17:52,356
lt's me. lt's just me.

1064
01:17:52,564 --> 01:17:56,523
l guess l haven't gotten over
my divorce yet, you know?

1065
01:17:56,734 --> 01:18:00,329
And also, l feel unsettled
about my career.

1066
01:18:00,538 --> 01:18:02,563
l'm very ambitious.

1067
01:18:02,774 --> 01:18:06,505
And that's an area that
l'd like to get consolidated.

1068
01:18:06,711 --> 01:18:09,475
l just feel, you know, unsettled.

1069
01:18:23,795 --> 01:18:25,160
Don't confuse me.

1070
01:18:25,363 --> 01:18:29,629
-l'm not trying to confuse you.
-l don't know what l'm doing.

1071
01:18:30,034 --> 01:18:33,197
l better go. l should just leave.

1072
01:18:33,404 --> 01:18:36,168
-You just got here.
-l know, but l--

1073
01:18:36,541 --> 01:18:40,944
-l'm sorry, l didn't mean--
-No, that's okay. l'll see you soon.

1074
01:18:41,145 --> 01:18:43,477
l'll just-- l'll be seeing you.

1075
01:18:47,318 --> 01:18:48,785
Please come in.

1076
01:18:50,455 --> 01:18:52,582
We read about it in the paper.

1077
01:18:52,790 --> 01:18:57,193
lt's a terrible thing.
She'd been coming here for years.

1078
01:18:57,395 --> 01:18:59,363
-Please, sit down.
-Thank you.

1079
01:19:00,164 --> 01:19:04,498
Just a few questions, doctor.
Records show she phoned you here...

1080
01:19:04,702 --> 01:19:07,569
...and at your home a number of times.

1081
01:19:07,772 --> 01:19:11,572
-She worried about her eyes.
-What was she suffering from?

1082
01:19:11,776 --> 01:19:16,804
Nothing serious. She had
light flashes, and they alarmed her.

1083
01:19:17,015 --> 01:19:19,449
l never found anything very wrong.

1084
01:19:19,651 --> 01:19:22,620
l told her it was just
a common occurrence.

1085
01:19:22,820 --> 01:19:26,620
-She was a hypochondriac?
-No. l wouldn't say that.

1086
01:19:26,824 --> 01:19:28,485
But she was concerned.

1087
01:19:29,160 --> 01:19:32,823
There's nothing she said
you think might be relevant?

1088
01:19:33,031 --> 01:19:34,828
Personal life? Friends?

1089
01:19:35,033 --> 01:19:37,001
No, not really.

1090
01:19:37,869 --> 01:19:39,769
How did she come to you?

1091
01:19:41,339 --> 01:19:45,002
l honestly can't remember.
Possibly another patient.

1092
01:19:45,209 --> 01:19:46,642
Can l get that name?

1093
01:19:46,844 --> 01:19:50,302
lt was a while ago,
and l treat so many patients.

1094
01:19:50,515 --> 01:19:53,348
-Might it be in your records?
-No.

1095
01:19:53,551 --> 01:19:56,543
No. l doubt it very much.

1096
01:19:57,455 --> 01:20:00,185
-Sorry to take up your time.
-That's okay.

1097
01:20:00,391 --> 01:20:03,292
lf you remember anything
that might help...

1098
01:20:03,494 --> 01:20:05,325
-...will you call me?
-Sure.

1099
01:20:05,530 --> 01:20:07,464
-Thank you.
-Pleasure.

1100
01:20:17,508 --> 01:20:19,305
You're having a breakdown!

1101
01:20:19,510 --> 01:20:23,071
They know she phoned me.
l lied. They saw through it.

1102
01:20:23,281 --> 01:20:26,682
-l can't take this.
-Pull yourself together.

1103
01:20:26,884 --> 01:20:30,012
l did it. lt's irrevocable,
and l'm gonna pay.

1104
01:20:30,221 --> 01:20:33,987
l had to fight an urge
to come clean to the police.

1105
01:20:34,192 --> 01:20:38,686
l'm in this with you. l helped you.
l don't wanna go to jail.

1106
01:20:38,896 --> 01:20:43,629
You get ideas about confessing,
and you'll drag me down with you.

1107
01:20:43,835 --> 01:20:45,803
But l won't let that happen.

1108
01:20:46,004 --> 01:20:49,371
-ls that a threat?
-Be a man. You're in the clear.

1109
01:20:49,574 --> 01:20:51,735
-You'll have me killed?
-Nonsense.

1110
01:20:51,943 --> 01:20:54,776
What did you mean by that remark?

1111
01:20:54,979 --> 01:20:57,573
You've helped me in the past. Fine.

1112
01:20:57,782 --> 01:20:59,807
l did you a favor. All right?

1113
01:21:00,018 --> 01:21:04,318
The time to confess was to Miriam
about your mistress.

1114
01:21:04,522 --> 01:21:06,854
Not about this! This is murder.

1115
01:21:07,058 --> 01:21:11,392
You paid for it, l engineered it.
lt's over! Forget about it!

1116
01:21:11,896 --> 01:21:15,457
-One sin leads to a deeper sin.
-You sound like Papa.

1117
01:21:15,667 --> 01:21:19,068
Adultery, fornication, lies, killing.

1118
01:21:19,270 --> 01:21:22,364
-Can you shut up?
-Or what? You'll shut me up?

1119
01:21:22,573 --> 01:21:25,633
One phone call,
like pushing a button right?

1120
01:22:02,191 --> 01:22:05,752
l don't know what's wrong
with you these days.

1121
01:22:06,862 --> 01:22:09,023
l believe in God, Miriam.

1122
01:22:09,898 --> 01:22:14,733
l know it. Because without God,
the world is a cesspool.

1123
01:22:14,937 --> 01:22:18,100
You drink every day.
You never used to.

1124
01:22:18,307 --> 01:22:19,865
lt's something new.

1125
01:22:20,075 --> 01:22:22,543
-God, it's hot.
-Maybe we should go--

1126
01:22:22,745 --> 01:22:26,579
-Don't tell me what to do, damn it!
-Will you calm down?

1127
01:22:29,451 --> 01:22:32,352
l don't feel well.
l'm gonna get some air.

1128
01:22:32,554 --> 01:22:34,283
No, you stay here.

1129
01:22:57,780 --> 01:23:01,272
This homeless story is too long,
I want five pages,

1130
01:23:01,483 --> 01:23:03,212
Five real pages,

1131
01:23:03,419 --> 01:23:07,446
His secretary types it tighter,
He doesn't take a thing out,

1132
01:23:07,656 --> 01:23:09,556
I want Johanson off the show,

1133
01:23:09,758 --> 01:23:13,854
He has cancer, Send him flowers,
He's not funny,

1134
01:23:14,063 --> 01:23:15,257
I want him off,

1135
01:23:15,464 --> 01:23:20,527
Can't anyone write funny anymore? I'm
supposed to write everything myself?

1136
01:23:20,736 --> 01:23:23,227
Write, direct and produce it myself?

1137
01:23:23,439 --> 01:23:27,671
I can't believe this!
Look at the people out there!

1138
01:23:27,876 --> 01:23:32,540
These people are looking for
something funny in their lives!

1139
01:23:32,748 --> 01:23:35,740
They're waiting for something funny!

1140
01:23:54,303 --> 01:23:56,134
This is terrible.

1141
01:23:56,405 --> 01:23:58,305
What are you doing to me?

1142
01:23:58,507 --> 01:24:01,408
This isn't a profile
of a creative mind!

1143
01:24:01,810 --> 01:24:06,804
It's tough for a woman in this
profession, Men always hit on them,

1144
01:24:07,015 --> 01:24:09,984
What is this? When did you shoot that?

1145
01:24:10,185 --> 01:24:13,643
l was lurking around the corner.
l couldn't resist.

1146
01:24:13,856 --> 01:24:16,324
I don't wanna do it
in a vulgar way,,,

1147
01:24:16,525 --> 01:24:19,289
,,,and take it off
from what I see here,

1148
01:24:19,495 --> 01:24:22,055
I wanna find out what's in here,

1149
01:24:22,264 --> 01:24:25,927
So I gotta spend some time,
have dinner together,

1150
01:24:26,135 --> 01:24:28,228
l'm taking over this film.

1151
01:24:28,437 --> 01:24:32,168
-You can't finish my film.
-l can't? Read your contract.

1152
01:24:32,374 --> 01:24:35,969
-You promised.
-The idea was to show the real me.

1153
01:24:36,178 --> 01:24:39,705
l'm not perfect, but l don't
promote values that--

1154
01:24:39,915 --> 01:24:41,280
Let me quote you:

1155
01:24:41,483 --> 01:24:44,281
''--deaden the sensibilities
of democracy.''

1156
01:24:44,486 --> 01:24:47,011
You're fired. Get out of here!

1157
01:24:47,222 --> 01:24:49,554
Go! Thank you! Goodbye!

1158
01:24:49,892 --> 01:24:54,090
If it bends, it's funny,
If it breaks, it isn't,

1159
01:24:55,030 --> 01:24:58,591
Don't get discouraged.
You have your own vision.

1160
01:24:58,801 --> 01:25:03,170
Why was he so mad? As if nobody
was ever compared to Mussolini.

1161
01:25:03,372 --> 01:25:08,503
l'd no idea you'd cut it like this. l
could've told you they'd never use it.

1162
01:25:08,710 --> 01:25:11,042
They want an upbeat profile.

1163
01:25:11,246 --> 01:25:14,807
He's gonna re-cut it
and make himself into a saint.

1164
01:25:15,017 --> 01:25:19,454
Wendy's right. l'm jealous of him
with his limos and his money.

1165
01:25:19,655 --> 01:25:23,421
-You have your own style.
-Listen. Marry me. l'm serious.

1166
01:25:23,625 --> 01:25:25,820
That's all l want. Marry me.

1167
01:25:26,028 --> 01:25:29,259
l'm crazy about you.
My marriage won't last.

1168
01:25:29,465 --> 01:25:33,265
l gotta talk to you.
Can we sit down for a second?

1169
01:25:33,469 --> 01:25:36,700
l'm not joking.
l'm really nuts about you.

1170
01:25:36,905 --> 01:25:38,805
l'm going away.

1171
01:25:41,043 --> 01:25:43,341
Yeah? Meaning what?

1172
01:25:44,146 --> 01:25:48,674
l've got a chance to produce
a couple of shows in London...

1173
01:25:48,884 --> 01:25:51,478
...and, you know, l couldn't say no.

1174
01:25:52,754 --> 01:25:57,384
-How long are you going for?
-Well, probably three or four months.

1175
01:25:57,926 --> 01:26:00,588
Three or four months?

1176
01:26:01,763 --> 01:26:05,927
Jesus. You're kidding.
What a discouraging thought.

1177
01:26:06,134 --> 01:26:08,227
But l think it's a good thing...

1178
01:26:08,437 --> 01:26:12,874
...because l need-- Well,
it will give me a little distance.

1179
01:26:13,075 --> 01:26:16,909
About 3000 miles, to be exact.
When are you leaving?

1180
01:26:17,112 --> 01:26:19,876
Oh, l guess 1 0 days or so.

1181
01:26:21,183 --> 01:26:22,650
God, l'm--

1182
01:26:27,656 --> 01:26:31,490
God, l'm gonna miss you.
l don't know what to say.

1183
01:26:32,528 --> 01:26:35,827
l'm not gonna see you
for three or four months?

1184
01:26:36,932 --> 01:26:41,460
l feel like l've, you know,
been handed a prison sentence.

1185
01:27:10,766 --> 01:27:14,224
Ben, your daughter
will make a beautiful bride.

1186
01:27:15,103 --> 01:27:18,630
This is Barbara,
the sister of my brother-in-law.

1187
01:27:19,241 --> 01:27:24,304
Congratulations. l wish
your daughter all the happiness.

1188
01:27:25,547 --> 01:27:26,536
Thank you.

1189
01:27:28,617 --> 01:27:33,247
Jesus, l'm so self-conscious.
Every single thing on me is rented:

1190
01:27:33,455 --> 01:27:36,515
A rented tux, rented shoes,
rented underwear.

1191
01:27:36,725 --> 01:27:38,955
You look fine. Do me a favor.

1192
01:27:39,161 --> 01:27:43,325
This is your last occasion
with my family. Let's get along.

1193
01:27:43,532 --> 01:27:45,966
Oh, and this is Dr. Rosenthal.

1194
01:27:46,168 --> 01:27:48,227
-l'm Miriam.
-This is Miriam.

1195
01:27:48,437 --> 01:27:50,405
This is Marian and Peter.

1196
01:27:50,606 --> 01:27:53,131
How do you do? lt's a pleasure.

1197
01:27:53,342 --> 01:27:55,367
-Judah?
-Yes, Ben?

1198
01:27:55,577 --> 01:27:58,740
l'm so glad you could make it.
lt means a lot.

1199
01:28:01,464 --> 01:28:04,956
What is the matter with you?
You seem so depressed.

1200
01:28:05,168 --> 01:28:08,604
Wendy and l finally
decided to call it quits.

1201
01:28:08,805 --> 01:28:13,640
Even though the last few years
have been terrible, it makes me sad.

1202
01:28:13,843 --> 01:28:16,368
-l'll have a vodka and tonic.
-Me too.

1203
01:28:16,579 --> 01:28:19,946
You told me it's been
platonic for a year.

1204
01:28:20,150 --> 01:28:22,448
Once the sex goes, it all goes.

1205
01:28:22,652 --> 01:28:27,715
Last time l was inside a woman was
when l visited the Statue of Liberty.

1206
01:28:36,366 --> 01:28:39,893
Your father's celebrating
enough for two people.

1207
01:28:40,103 --> 01:28:43,869
He and Ben will get high
and argue about belief in God.

1208
01:28:44,073 --> 01:28:46,337
My dad takes after his Aunt May.

1209
01:28:46,543 --> 01:28:51,503
She rejected the Bible because it had
an unbelievable sense of character.

1210
01:28:52,215 --> 01:28:57,016
l walked in. l said, ''The Waldorf
Astoria.'' You see the centerpieces?

1211
01:28:57,220 --> 01:29:00,212
Did you see the matches?
Lester paid for it.

1212
01:29:00,423 --> 01:29:03,824
l can't believe a brother
would pay for a wedding.

1213
01:29:04,027 --> 01:29:07,428
That's the sort of thing
Lester's always doing.

1214
01:29:07,630 --> 01:29:12,590
-You've known him for a long time?
-Since high school.

1215
01:29:25,915 --> 01:29:29,009
They're pretty.
They're very, very pretty.

1216
01:29:29,219 --> 01:29:31,187
-Hi, Cliff.
-Cliff, hello.

1217
01:29:31,387 --> 01:29:34,015
Lester, how are you? Good to see you.

1218
01:29:34,224 --> 01:29:37,887
-My fiancée, Halley.
-Congratulations. My wife, Nancy.

1219
01:29:38,862 --> 01:29:41,456
-Jesus, you look wonderful.
-Thank you.

1220
01:29:42,131 --> 01:29:43,598
When did you return?

1221
01:29:44,033 --> 01:29:47,764
l got back this morning.
l've been trying to call you.

1222
01:29:47,971 --> 01:29:51,236
l finally won her heart.
What a romantic story.

1223
01:29:51,441 --> 01:29:53,466
We saw each other in London.

1224
01:29:53,676 --> 01:29:56,839
l sent her white roses
around the clock...

1225
01:29:57,046 --> 01:30:01,107
...all the time, for days.
Then l found out she was allergic.

1226
01:30:01,317 --> 01:30:03,444
-Hi.
-Hi. Congratulations.

1227
01:30:03,653 --> 01:30:04,881
Good to see you.

1228
01:30:05,088 --> 01:30:07,454
So l started pleading with her.

1229
01:30:07,657 --> 01:30:10,285
l just begged her day and night.

1230
01:30:10,493 --> 01:30:13,485
And l think it was
the caviar that did it.

1231
01:30:13,696 --> 01:30:16,164
l've envied this guy for years.

1232
01:30:16,366 --> 01:30:19,858
He'd show up with a beautiful woman
all the time.

1233
01:30:20,069 --> 01:30:23,038
-But l envy you more now.
-Thank you.

1234
01:30:49,365 --> 01:30:52,027
Standing here
in the presence of God...

1235
01:30:52,235 --> 01:30:56,569
...the guardian of our homes,
ready to enter the bonds of wedlock...

1236
01:30:56,773 --> 01:31:00,265
...answer each of you,
in reverence for God...

1237
01:31:00,476 --> 01:31:03,673
...and in hearing of
the assembly gathered here...

1238
01:31:03,880 --> 01:31:06,314
...so joyously with you.

1239
01:31:14,757 --> 01:31:16,850
-l know the perfect guy.
-Who?

1240
01:31:17,060 --> 01:31:21,019
-He's brilliant, attractive.
-There's a hitch. l'm waiting.

1241
01:31:21,230 --> 01:31:25,223
There is, but it sounds worse
than it is. He's in prison.

1242
01:31:25,435 --> 01:31:29,132
-That's a drawback.
-Nothing terrible. lnsider trading.

1243
01:31:29,339 --> 01:31:33,002
He made a fortune in the market.
He'll be out soon.

1244
01:31:33,209 --> 01:31:35,404
Very soon. A couple of years.

1245
01:31:35,611 --> 01:31:37,738
You mean with good behavior.

1246
01:31:56,532 --> 01:31:58,796
l wanted to talk to you.

1247
01:32:04,140 --> 01:32:09,442
What is there really to say?
You know, l'm just stunned still.

1248
01:32:12,181 --> 01:32:15,548
He's not what you think.
He's wonderful.

1249
01:32:15,752 --> 01:32:19,017
He's warm and caring...

1250
01:32:19,222 --> 01:32:23,181
-...and romantic.
-He's a success, that's what he is.

1251
01:32:23,393 --> 01:32:27,261
-He's rich and he's a success.
-Give me a little credit.

1252
01:32:27,463 --> 01:32:30,955
l always did give you
a little credit until today.

1253
01:32:31,167 --> 01:32:36,161
We used to laugh at him. The silly
shows he puts on, the way he talks.

1254
01:32:36,372 --> 01:32:38,306
He's endearing.

1255
01:32:39,742 --> 01:32:43,041
This is my worst fear realized.

1256
01:32:48,584 --> 01:32:51,246
l wanted to give you this letter back.

1257
01:32:54,757 --> 01:32:57,851
-lt's my one love letter.
-lt's beautiful.

1258
01:32:58,061 --> 01:33:00,689
l'm just the wrong person.

1259
01:33:04,400 --> 01:33:06,493
lt's probably just as well.

1260
01:33:08,471 --> 01:33:11,565
l plagiarized most of it
from James Joyce.

1261
01:33:12,909 --> 01:33:16,401
You probably wondered
about the Dublin references.

1262
01:33:18,281 --> 01:33:21,808
l hope we can always be friends.

1263
01:34:06,013 --> 01:34:09,414
Off by yourself, huh? You're like me.

1264
01:34:10,584 --> 01:34:13,382
l always get sad at these events.

1265
01:34:13,587 --> 01:34:15,646
You look very deep in thought.

1266
01:34:18,525 --> 01:34:20,959
l was plotting the perfect murder.

1267
01:34:23,464 --> 01:34:24,954
Movie plot?

1268
01:34:25,899 --> 01:34:27,196
Movie?

1269
01:34:28,335 --> 01:34:32,237
That's what Ben told me.
He says you make films.

1270
01:34:32,439 --> 01:34:36,773
Yeah, but not that kind.
You know, a different kind.

1271
01:34:38,545 --> 01:34:40,945
l have a great murder story.

1272
01:34:42,249 --> 01:34:44,547
-Yes?
-A great plot.

1273
01:34:45,552 --> 01:34:46,883
Yeah.

1274
01:34:48,856 --> 01:34:52,587
Hey, l've had too many to drink.
l mean, forgive me.

1275
01:34:52,793 --> 01:34:54,920
l know you want your privacy.

1276
01:34:55,129 --> 01:34:59,463
No, it's okay.
l'm not doing anything special.

1277
01:35:00,033 --> 01:35:05,369
Except my murder story
has a very strange twist.

1278
01:35:07,174 --> 01:35:08,471
Yeah?

1279
01:35:10,244 --> 01:35:14,408
Let's say there's this man
who is very successful.

1280
01:35:14,615 --> 01:35:16,344
He has everything.

1281
01:35:23,891 --> 01:35:26,086
-Let me ask you something.
-What?

1282
01:35:26,293 --> 01:35:28,261
-Am l a phony?
-Are you what?

1283
01:35:28,462 --> 01:35:31,556
-Am l a phony?
-Are you a little high?

1284
01:35:32,199 --> 01:35:33,689
-He hates me.
-Who?

1285
01:35:33,901 --> 01:35:38,065
Your annoying husband.
Every time l'm with him, l get tense.

1286
01:35:38,272 --> 01:35:40,467
-He's angry.
-At what?

1287
01:35:40,674 --> 01:35:41,800
Are you kidding?

1288
01:35:42,009 --> 01:35:45,410
He's got these fantasies
about changing the world.

1289
01:35:45,612 --> 01:35:48,240
ln the end, his films come to nothing.

1290
01:35:48,448 --> 01:35:52,578
He's gotta grow up.
This is the real world, the big time.

1291
01:35:52,786 --> 01:35:56,620
They don't pay for high aspirations.
You gotta deliver.

1292
01:35:56,824 --> 01:36:00,419
Not to mention the fact that--
You're still young.

1293
01:36:00,627 --> 01:36:04,859
-You're not getting what you deserve.
-Lester, l met somebody.

1294
01:36:08,068 --> 01:36:10,229
That is music to my ears.

1295
01:36:12,005 --> 01:36:14,496
And after the awful deed is done...

1296
01:36:14,708 --> 01:36:18,144
...he finds that he's plagued
by deep-rooted guilt.

1297
01:36:18,345 --> 01:36:21,803
Little sparks of
his religious background...

1298
01:36:22,015 --> 01:36:26,076
...which he'd rejected,
are suddenly stirred up.

1299
01:36:27,521 --> 01:36:30,513
He hears his father's voice.

1300
01:36:30,858 --> 01:36:34,726
He imagines that God
is watching his every move.

1301
01:36:34,928 --> 01:36:37,795
Suddenly, it's not
an empty universe...

1302
01:36:37,998 --> 01:36:40,831
...but a just and moral one...

1303
01:36:41,134 --> 01:36:43,159
...and he's violated it.

1304
01:36:43,837 --> 01:36:46,067
Now he's panic-stricken.

1305
01:36:46,340 --> 01:36:49,036
He's on the verge
of a mental collapse.

1306
01:36:49,243 --> 01:36:53,703
An inch away from confessing
the whole thing to the police.

1307
01:36:54,748 --> 01:36:57,808
And then one morning...

1308
01:36:58,018 --> 01:36:59,849
...he awakens...

1309
01:37:00,454 --> 01:37:04,185
...and the sun is shining,
and his family is around him.

1310
01:37:04,391 --> 01:37:08,555
Mysteriously, the crisis is lifted.

1311
01:37:10,197 --> 01:37:14,497
He takes his family to Europe
and as the months pass...

1312
01:37:14,701 --> 01:37:16,669
...he finds he's not punished.

1313
01:37:17,070 --> 01:37:19,061
ln fact, he prospers.

1314
01:37:19,673 --> 01:37:22,369
The killing's attributed
to a drifter...

1315
01:37:22,576 --> 01:37:25,067
...who has many murders to his credit.

1316
01:37:25,279 --> 01:37:28,043
What the hell,
one more doesn't matter.

1317
01:37:28,715 --> 01:37:30,808
Now he's scot-free.

1318
01:37:31,351 --> 01:37:34,684
His life is completely
back to normal...

1319
01:37:35,222 --> 01:37:39,921
...back to his protected world
of wealth and privilege.

1320
01:37:40,294 --> 01:37:43,855
Yes, but can he ever really go back?

1321
01:37:45,732 --> 01:37:49,668
Well, people carry sins
around with them, l mean....

1322
01:37:49,870 --> 01:37:54,603
Oh, maybe once in a while
he has a bad moment, but it passes.

1323
01:37:55,008 --> 01:37:57,875
And with time, it all fades.

1324
01:37:58,345 --> 01:38:00,677
Yeah, but-- So then, you know--

1325
01:38:00,881 --> 01:38:04,612
Then his worst beliefs are realized.

1326
01:38:04,818 --> 01:38:07,787
l said it was
a chilling story, didn't l?

1327
01:38:09,856 --> 01:38:13,485
l think it'd be tough for
somebody to live with that.

1328
01:38:13,694 --> 01:38:17,926
Very few guys could actually live
with something like that.

1329
01:38:18,131 --> 01:38:22,067
People carry awful deeds with them.
What should he do?

1330
01:38:22,269 --> 01:38:23,827
Turn himself in?

1331
01:38:24,404 --> 01:38:26,235
l mean, this is reality.

1332
01:38:26,440 --> 01:38:28,533
ln reality, we rationalize.

1333
01:38:28,742 --> 01:38:32,109
We deny, or we couldn't go on living.

1334
01:38:35,515 --> 01:38:38,609
l would have him turn himself in...

1335
01:38:38,819 --> 01:38:42,414
...because then your story
assumes tragic proportions.

1336
01:38:42,622 --> 01:38:44,920
Because in the absence of a God...

1337
01:38:45,125 --> 01:38:48,288
...he is forced to assume
that responsibility.

1338
01:38:48,495 --> 01:38:50,827
Then you have tragedy.

1339
01:38:51,164 --> 01:38:54,190
But that's fiction,
that's movies. l mean--

1340
01:38:54,401 --> 01:38:58,497
You see too many movies.
l'm talking about reality.

1341
01:38:58,705 --> 01:39:02,732
lf you want a happy ending,
go see a Hollywood movie.

1342
01:39:04,344 --> 01:39:08,371
Come on, darling.
Let's think about going home, huh?

1343
01:39:08,582 --> 01:39:10,777
Nice talking to you. Good luck.

1344
01:39:10,984 --> 01:39:15,318
We'll have a wedding like this
for Sharon, and l can't wait.

1345
01:39:15,522 --> 01:39:17,752
She'll be radiant.

1346
01:39:18,091 --> 01:39:22,687
-You're looking very handsome tonight.
-And you look beautiful.

1347
01:39:46,153 --> 01:39:49,384
We are all faced
throughout our lives,,,

1348
01:39:49,589 --> 01:39:52,023
,,,with agonizing decisions,,,

1349
01:39:52,225 --> 01:39:54,216
,,,moral choices,

1350
01:39:54,428 --> 01:39:57,329
Some are on a grand scale,

1351
01:39:57,531 --> 01:40:01,763
Most of these choices
are on lesser points,

1352
01:40:02,803 --> 01:40:07,866
But we define ourselves
by the choices we have made,

1353
01:40:08,075 --> 01:40:13,035
We are, in fact,
the sum total of our choices,

1354
01:40:13,346 --> 01:40:16,645
Events unfold so unpredictably,,,

1355
01:40:17,050 --> 01:40:19,245
,,,so unfairly,,,

1356
01:40:19,453 --> 01:40:23,583
,,,human happiness does not seem
to have been included,,,

1357
01:40:23,790 --> 01:40:26,190
,,,in the design of Creation,

1358
01:40:26,393 --> 01:40:30,887
It is only we,
with our capacity to love,,,

1359
01:40:31,098 --> 01:40:34,898
,,, that give meaning
to the indifferent universe,

1360
01:40:35,302 --> 01:40:38,499
And yet, most human beings,,,

1361
01:40:38,705 --> 01:40:42,607
,,,seem to have the ability
to keep trying,,,

1362
01:40:42,809 --> 01:40:47,075
,,,and even to find joy
from simple things,,,

1363
01:40:47,280 --> 01:40:50,010
,,,like their family,,,

1364
01:40:50,217 --> 01:40:51,912
,,, their work,,,

1365
01:40:52,119 --> 01:40:53,711
,,,and from the hope,,,

1366
01:40:53,920 --> 01:40:56,616
,,, that future generations,,,

1367
01:40:56,823 --> 01:41:00,020
,,,might understand more,

